						               													<description>Geni (Genius) is a classic trivia game in Norway. Since its original release in 1986, the game has been re-released about every three years, and has also been remade in different themes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The current rules have been fixed since the second edition (1993), and the game consits of three stages:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1st stage: Answer (at least) one question from each category correctly&amp;#10;2nd stage: Answer two questions from two categories dictated by the board (depending on which route you choose to the center)&amp;#10;3rd stage: Answer one question from a category decided by the player to the left&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player to complete the last stage wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;List of editions:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     1986 (528 cards with 3168 questions): Had different 2nd and 3rd stages. (The last stage was answering three questions correctly IN SUCCESSION)&amp;#10;     1989 Released as Geni: Pop &amp; Rock&amp;#10;     1993 (400 cards). The current rules were settled. Categories: Geography, Sports and Entertainment, Nature and Science, 1 X 2 (multiple choice), History, and Mixed&amp;#10;     1997 (500 cards) Categories: As in 1993 ed, but replaced 1 X 2 with Events from '96-97&amp;#10;     1997 (132 cards) Expansion pack, also playable as stand-alone.&amp;#10;     2000 (500 cards), named Gull Geni. Categories: As in 1993 ed, but replaced 1 X 2 with 20th Century, and Mixed with Modern Music&amp;#10;     2003 (470 cards, plus 30 Stroke of Genius cards) Categories: As in 1993 ed, but replaced 1 X 2 with From 1900 to current time. (The stroke of genius cards is a joker category.)&amp;#10;     2003 Travel edition&amp;#10;     2005 New edition of Geni: Pop &amp; Rock&amp;#10;     2006 (376 cards, plus 24 Stroke of Genius cards) New categories: TV and Entertainment, Norway, Culture and History, Our world, Sports and Leisure, Mixed&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Geni is also featured in a series of childrens editions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
